   "body" : "This PR adds some sanity checking to `DecodeHexTx` to make sure that the scripts contain valid opcodes. The main purpose of doing this is to avoid decoding witness transactions as 0-input 1-output non-witness transactions. The scripts are likely to be garbage and contain invalid opcodes when decoded as non-witness.\r\n\r\nThere is an issue where other invalid opcodes (not just OP_INVALIDOPCODE) are not handled but I am not sure how to go about doing that.\r\n\r\nThis is related to #9522. ",
